
[1]squarrous

   SQUARROUS, a. [Gr., scurf.] In botany, scurfy or ragged, or full of
   scales; rough; jagged. A squarrous calyx consists of scales very sidely
   divaricating; a squarrous leaf is divided into shreds or jags, raised
   above the plane of the leaf, and not parallel to it.
